cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.NA, cs.SP

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a system for analog-to-information conversion using a continuous-time chaotic system, which falls under the scope of systems and control.
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with compressive measurements and sparse signal reconstruction, which are topics related to information theory.
- cs.DS (Dynamical Systems): The paper uses a chaotic system to generate the compressive measurements and reconstruct the sparse signal, which falls under the scope of dynamical systems.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper discusses the sparsity-regularized nonlinear least squares estimation, which is a topic related to numerical analysis.
- cs.SP (Signal Processing): The paper deals with the acquisition and reconstruction of analog signals, which falls under the scope of signal processing.
